lank1_info = \n|website = \n|footnotes = \n}}\n\n'''Mwanza''' is a town in [[Malawi]] on the border with [[Mozambique]]. It is the administrative headquarters for [[Mwanza District]].<ref name=\"2R\">{{google maps| url=https://www.google.com/maps/place/15%C2%B035'55.0%22S+34%C2%B031'04.0%22E/@-15.5992174,34.5058354,4941m/data=!3m1!1e3!4m5!3m4!1s0x0:0x0!8m2!3d-15.5986111!4d34.5177778 |title=Location of Mwanza, Mwanza District, Southern Region, Malawi |access-date=4 May 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Location==\nMwanza is the largest commercial, political and administrative urban centre of Mwanza District, in the [[Southern Region, Malawi |Southern Region]] of Malawi. It lies on the important road from [[Blantyre]] to [[Tete]] in Mozambique, approximately {{convert|100|km|0}}, by road, northwest of Blantyre, Malawi's commercial capital.<ref name=\"3R\">{{google maps| url=https://www.google.com/maps/dir/Blantyre,+Malawi/Mwanza,+Malawi/@-15.6114018,34.5382491,10z/data=!4m14!4m13!1m5!1m1!1s0x18d84513cbc0005f:0x236358dae4d811e6!2m2!1d35.0167866!2d-15.7666707!1m5!1m1!1s0x18d88194a1aa95a3:0x65ae32b09a13ab25!2m2!1d34.5140637!2d-15.5997929!3e0 |title=Distance Between Blantyre, Malawi And Mwanza, Malawi |access-date=4 May 2020}}</ref> The geographical coordinates of Mwanza, Malawi are:15\u00b035'55.0\"S, 34\u00b031'04.0\"E (Latitude:-15.598611; Longitude:34.517778).<ref name=\"2R\"/> The town sits at an average elevation of {{convert|626|m|0}} above sea level.<ref name=\"4R\">{{cite web| url=https://www.floodmap.net/Elevation/ElevationMap/?gi=925596 | title=Elevation of Mwanza, Malawi |publisher=Floodmap.net | date=4 May 2020 |author=Floodmap |access-date=4 May 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Population==\nThe national census and household survey conducted in 2018, enumerated the population of Mwanza, Malawi at 18,039 inhabitants.\nThe majority of people in the town and the district belong to the [[Chewa people|Chewa ethnic group]].<ref name=\"1R\">{{cite web| publisher=Malawi National Statistical Office |date=May 2019 | url=http://www.nsomalawi.mw/images/stories/data_on_line/demography/census_2018/2018%20Malawi%20Population%20and%20Housing%20Census%20Main%20Report.pdf |title=2018 Population and Housing Census Main Report |author=Malawi National Statistical Office |access-date=4 May 2020 |place=Lilongwe}}</ref>\n\n==Economy==\nThe town is a market town for local produce, including honey, as well as a distribution market for commercial products and processed foods, such as maize flour. Mwanza also acts as a transshipment point for goods going down the [[Zambeze River]] via Tete. It is also a centre for smuggling.<ref name=\"5R\">{{cite web|url=https://www.cehurd.org/arvs-smuggled-to-south-africa/ | title=ARVS Smuggled To South Africa |publisher=Center for Health, Human Rights and Development (CEHURD) |date=26 August 2012 |access-date=4 May 2020 |author=Wezzie Nkhoma-Somba |location=Kampala}}</ref> In 2007, Ethiopian illegal immigrants were discovered hidden in an oil tanker at Mwanza, Malawi, at the border with Mozambique, on their way to South Africa. In July 2012, 49 Ethiopian and Somali nationals drowned \nin [[Lake Malawi]] when the boat in which they were attempting to cross the lake capsized. The group which started in Tanzania, had intended to cross into Mozambique and finally to South Africa.<ref name=\"6R\">{{cite web|publisher=[[Nyasa Times]] | url=https://www.hiiraan.com/news4/2012/july/25005/police_nab_4th_suspect_charged_with_manslaughter.aspx |title=Police Nab 4th Suspect, Charged With Manslaughter |date=16 July 2012 | author=Felie Mzumara |access-date=4 May 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Infrastructure==\nMwanza has an airstrip with a {{convert|1000|m|0}} long runway.  It has both primary and secondary schools as well as a hospital. Mwanza District Hospital serves not only the local district, but also neighbouring [[Chikwawa District]] and [[Neno District]] in Malawi and the town of Zobue and [[Moatize District]] across the border in Mozambique.<ref name\"7R\">{{cite web|date=26 July 2012 | url=https://www.nyasatimes.com/vp-kachali-makes-surprise-visit-to-mwanza-hospital/ |title=Vice President Kachali Makes Surprise Visit To Mwanza District Hospital |publisher=[[Nyasa Times]] | author=Nyasa Times |access-date=4 May 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.flickr.com/photos/63264458@N05/6832482288/ Photo: Border Operations Assessment Mwanza-Zobue Border Posts] As of 23 June 2011.\n* [https://www.flickr.com/photos/oudinafrika/4042370157/sizes/o/in/photostream/ Photo: Mwanza District Hospital] As of 20 October 2009.\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Populated places in Malawi]]\n[[Category:Populated places in Southern Region, Malawi]]\n[[Category:Malawi\u2013Mozambique border crossings]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Town in Malawi}}\n\n{{EngvarB|date=May 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2020}}\n{{Infobox settlement \n<!--See the Table at Infobox Settlement for all fields and descriptions of usage--> \n<!-- Basic info ----------------> |official_name = Malawi\n|other_name = \n|native_name =   <!-- for cities whose native name is not in English --> \n|nickname = \n|settlement_type = <!--For Town or Village (Leave blank for the default City)--> \n|motto = \n<!-- images and maps -----------> \n|image_skyline = \n|imagesize = 250px\n|image_caption = \n|image_flag = \n|flag_size = \n|image_seal = \n|seal_size = \n|image_shield = \n|shield_size = \n|image_blank_emblem = \n|blank_emblem_type = \n|blank_emblem_size = \n|image_map = \n|mapsize = \n|map_caption = \n|image_map1 = \n|mapsize1 = \n|map_caption1 = \n|image_dot_map = \n|dot_mapsize = \n|dot_map_caption = \n|dot_x = \n|dot_y = \n|pushpin_map = Malawi<!-- the name of a location map as per http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Template:Location_map --> \n|pushpin_mapsize=240\n|pushpin_label_position =bottom \n|pushpin_map_caption = Location in Malawi\n<!-- Location ------------------> \n|subdivision_type = Country \n|subdivision_name 